Author: felipe
Content: I understand your argument, but at the same time I believe that in order to bring the "big stuff" to reality that truly impacts people lives, it requires heavy high-risk investment that only few organizations can absorb (normally governments). For example, the Wright Brothers succeeded because the military invested heavily in the first airplanes. Other examples are the Internet, the space program, cars (highway investment), commercial airlines, etc... A lot of the big stuff is initially subsidized with public money, and then thrown to the private sector.
